<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-158-276  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 158 276.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  April 3 1989 v6 n13 p33(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CD-ROM adds SCSI interface; OEMs expected to snap it up. (smallcomputer systems interface)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grygo, Gene.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Laser Magnetic Storage International Co. (products).andO;Product:   DEC VAX (Minicomputer)LMSI CM 212 (Disk storage device).andO;Topic:     CD-ROMEmbedded SystemsSmall Computer Systems InterfaceOEMsAdd-In-On Devices.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CD-ROM Adds SCSI Interface; OEMs Expected To Snap It UpandM;COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo.andP;  -- A recently introduced CD-ROM drive from LaserMagnetic Storage (LMS) marks the first time an American manufacturer hasoffered such a drive with an embedded SCSI interface.andM;But VAX/VMS users might have to wait a while for the CM 212.andP;  Direct sales ofthe product will only be a small part of its distribution.andP;  The CM 212 isgeared primarily for the OEM and systems integration markets.andM;It's likely that VAX users will have to wait for systems integrators beforethey can include the CM 212 in their environments, LMS officials said.andM;In theory, there should be no problems for the end user who buys the unitdirectly, said Robert Van Eijk, the company's product sales manager forCD-ROM.andP;  &quot;But I can't guarantee that,&quot; he said.andP;  &quot;It hasn't been tested onVAXes.&quot;andP;  VAX users who forego a systems integrator might have to makesoftware adjustments, he said.andM;&quot;But for a systems integrator, it should not be too much trouble,&quot; Van Eijksaid.andM;Other features of the drive include a mean-time-between-failure rating of40,000 hours, an access time of 400 milliseconds and a 64KB buffer.andP;  The SCSIinterface allows the unit to interface with workstations from DEC, Apple, Sunand Apollo.andM;&quot;Because LMS is the only U.S.-based manufacturer of this type of product,several government suppliers are not evaluating our drive,&quot; said John Hoy,vice president of marketing for the LMS Optical Storage Division.andM;The CM 212 is available in sample quantities with full production to startlater this month.andP;  It is scheduled to be shipped next month with OEM pricingat $875.andM;Laser Magnetic Storage International Co. is located at 4425 Arrows WestDrive, Colorado Springs, CO 80907-3489, (719) 593-7900.andO;</TEXT></DOC>